Federal power was also used selectively against states and localities. North Carolina\'92s request for extended FEMA aid after Hurricane Helene was denied, despite ongoing recovery needs. Maine was threatened with the loss of education and school lunch funding over its transgender sports policy. Title X family planning funds\'97about $66 million\'97were frozen for clinics serving more than two million people, many of them low\uc0\u8209 income women and minorities, under the guise of compliance reviews. The Department of Justice canceled an environmental justice settlement with Alabama that had required the state to stop criminally prosecuting poor residents for lacking proper sewage systems in Lowndes County, and to address the health risks of raw sewage exposure. These decisions did not simply reflect policy preferences. They showed federal resources being used as punishment for jurisdictions and communities that did not align with the administration\'92s priorities. Geography and policy stance now shaped access to basic support.\
